+sdlmame for Debian
+------------------
+
+The differences with the upstream behaviour are file locations and executable
+name.
+
+*   Building directly from source, you get a mame<xxx> executable file, where
+    <xxx> depends on building target and optimizations. In this package you
+    get a sdlmame executable with a mame symlink pointing to it (basically for
+    frontends compatibility).
+
+*   The default .ini files are in /etc/sdlmame/, but you can still use the
+    -inipath /path/to/a/different/mame.ini command line option if you wish. A
+    pristine copy of each files also lies in /usr/share/doc/sdlmame/examples/,
+    just in case you need them.
+
+*   The same directory also hosts the sdlmame-specific joystick.dat file, a
+    useful feature when you own many USB controller. See manpage for details.
+
+*   as roms are copyrighted material, a set of path is defined in the default
+    mame.ini file to handle it as clean as possible
+    *   personal user roms should be put in $HOME/.mame/roms/
+    *   system-wide roms (i.e. the ones which every user may use, like freely
+        available ones) should be put in /usr/local/share/games/sdlmame/roms/
+
+*   the same applies for samples and artworks (obviously in the ..../samples/
+    and ..../artwork/ directories); even though they can be freely downloaded
+    from the official MAME(tm) site and used system-wide, you can use your
+    own if you like it.
+
+*   output directories (inp, nvram, memcard etc.) lie in /var/games/sdlmame/
+
+*   the ctrlr directory is a configuration one, so it lies in /etc/sdlmame/
+    instead
+
+*   keymap files are in /usr/share/games/sdlmame/keymaps/, but you'll need
+    to specify the full path to them with the -keymap_file line option
+
+*   tools (romcmp, chdman, etc.) are in an optional separate package
+    (sdlmame-tools)
+
+
+Important notice: Due to a deep change in input core during the 0.118
+development cycle, .cfg file format has changed breaking compatibility.
+Upgrading from earlier versions will sweep out your /var/games/sdlmame/cfg
+directory.
+
+Have fun!
+
+ -- Cesare Falco <cesare.falco@gmail.com>, Sun, 20 Sep 2007 15:24:00 +0200
